      "content": "When your noise looks structured, it suggests you might have more than just random measurement error; you might have lurking variables or systematic issues. You can try to model this chaotic interference by using more robust statistical methods, such as non-parametric tests or incorporating external variables into a regression model. If the outliers are truly influential, you might need to investigate them thoroughly—are they errors, or do they represent a real subgroup effect? Analyzing the data with different assumptions about its structure can help you determine if the \"messiness\" is random noise or a signal you're missing.",
